With the official Earth Day celebration happening tomorrow, I wanted to share additional air quality improvement photos from around the world.

Because of COVID-19, the earth has been able to press the reset button. There's been record-low oil consumption and astonishing air quality improvement.

The Himalayas are now visible from Nepal and India for the first time in many, many years. This is one unexpected, yet positive aspect of the quarantine. My hope is that this improvement will encourage us all to pay more attention to the quality of the air and to celebrate the earth with each day as opposed to just once a year.
